tional studies and earned a graduate certificate in non proliferation studies she has a particular interest in middle eastern politics and security issues while a graduate student zhila worked as a research assistant for the james martin center for nonproliferation studies writing and editing for the nuclear threat initiative prior to graduate school she was an analyst with the university of california's education abroad program zhila holds a bachelor's degree in international relations from uc davis and participated in the uc in dc internship program and a year long study abroad in bordeaux france search cisac people everything support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9625 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
